Dear Resident,
I am honoured to be your Labour candidate for Queen's Park and Maida
Vale. Residents from Harlesden to Westbourne have told me that they want
to see national change.
We see every day the chaos and devastation under this Tory Government.
It is everywhere, from the hours I spent waiting in A&E with my
grandparents at St Mary's Hospital to the parents I meet forced to skip
meals to feed their children.
If elected I will be a community MP, working every day to make sure the
residents of Queen's Park and Maida Vale are seeing change - more
teachers in schools, more opportunities for young people, more homes
local people can afford, safer streets and reduced NHS waiting times.
Georgia Gould
Georgia's Story
My family have lived around this area for generations. My great
grandfather came to this country as a teenager, working his way up to
open a shop on Kilburn High Road. My mum grew up off Edgware Road and I
grew up on Westbourne Park Road. I will work every day to give back to
the community that has given my family so many opportunities.
Promoted by Marc Harris on behalf of Georgia Gould, both at 4G Shirland
Mews, London, W9 3DY.
